{"id": "1414676585772093622", "channel_id": "1414676585772093622", "type": 0, "author_id": "120677325137379328", "author_name": "crimsondream24", "author_bot": false, "content": "A couple of patches ago in the English translation for the game long messages were given a scroll instead of continuing on a second window and I would like to request this change be reverted. The scroll has become problematic in several ways.\n\nScenario 1: The text often scrolls before the player is given time to properly take in what has been said, requiring the player to check the logs to re-read it and breaking immersion.\n\nScenario 2: The game does not allow you to proceed to the next dialogue box until the scroll has finished. This becomes a problem when simple, easy to understand sentences are written and you want to advance to the next dialogue window but have to wait for the scroll to finish in order to do so.\n\nBoth of these scenarios are very obnoxious and have a negative impact on the experience of players and were not a problem with the old system of spilling over into a new dialogue window. I know that I am not the only player bothered by this, I have seen several others complain about this feature; including players new to the game who hadn't played using the old system. Please revert this change to maintain immersion in the story.", "timestamp": "2025-09-08T18:19:41.468000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 14}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414676585772093622", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Dialogue Scroll Was a Mistake", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
